<%- view_title "NICE Work Roles" %>

<% content_for :main do %>
<h1>NICE Work Roles <span class="badge badge-pill badge-secondary"><%= @nice_work_roles.count%></span></h1>
<blockquote class="blockquote">
  <p class="mb-0">Work roles are the most detailed groupings of cybersecurity and related work which include a list of attributes required to perform that role in the form of knowledge, skills, and abilities (KSAs) and tasks performed in that role.</p>
  <footer class="blockquote-footer"><cite title="NIST SP 800-181">NIST SP 800-181</cite></footer>
</blockquote>

<h2>Interconnections</h2>
<p>NICE work roles share common knowledge, skills, abilities, and tasks. The arc diagrams below illustrates the interconnectedness of work roles, which can help conceptualize career paths, progressions, etc.</p>

<h3>Knowledge</h3>
<%= nice_work_roles_arc_diagram(@similarity_map, :shared_knowledge) %>

<h3>Skills</h3>
<%= nice_work_roles_arc_diagram(@similarity_map, :shared_skills) %>

<h3>Abilities</h3>
<%= nice_work_roles_arc_diagram(@similarity_map, :shared_abilities) %>

<h3>Tasks</h3>
<%= nice_work_roles_arc_diagram(@similarity_map, :shared_tasks) %>

<h2>Inventory</h2>
<%= nice_work_roles_table(@nice_work_roles) %>

<% end %>
